---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Work With Me — Matt Sanford" screenLabel="04 Work With Me" active="work">
  <section class="pagehead">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Work With Me</span>
      <h1>Three ways in. All of them start with an assessment.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        No countdown timers. No transformation challenges. No twelve-week
        PDFs. Just a careful look at your body and a coach who shows up every
        week.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tiers">
        <article class="tier">
          <span class="meta">Tier i</span>
          <h3>Movement Assessment</h3>
          <p class="price"><small>90 minutes · one-time</small></p>
          <p style="color: var(--granite); font-size: 15px; margin: 0;">
            The front door. Posture, breath, primal patterns, FMS — and a
            written plan in plain English. Yours to keep with or without me.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Full intake conversation</li>
            <li>Breath &amp; posture analysis</li>
            <li>7-pattern + FMS movement screen</li>
            <li>Written summary &amp; next-steps plan</li>
            <li>One follow-up question, free, by email</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-ghost">
            Book the assessment <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>

        <article class="tier featured">
          <span class="meta">Tier ii · Most chosen</span>
          <h3>Ongoing Coaching</h3>
          <p class="price"><small>Monthly · in-person</small></p>
          <p style="color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--dune) 88%, transparent); font-size: 15px; margin: 0;">
            Two sessions a week at the gym, plus programming for the days I'm
            not there. The whole point is steady — across years, not weeks.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>2× weekly in-person sessions</li>
            <li>Custom programming for off-days</li>
            <li>Quarterly reassessment</li>
            <li>Sleep &amp; recovery check-ins</li>
            <li>Text-line access for adjustments</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn" style="background: var(--paper); color: var(--forest-deep);">
            Start coaching <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>

        <article class="tier">
          <span class="meta">Tier iii</span>
          <h3>Train for the Trail</h3>
          <p class="price"><small>12-week block</small></p>
          <p style="color: var(--granite); font-size: 15px; margin: 0;">
            Built for a specific peak or a specific season. Eccentric loading,
            Zone 2, intervals, and the unglamorous prep work that turns a hard
            day on the mountain into a sustainable one.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>12-week periodized block</li>
            <li>Strength, cardio, &amp; descent prep</li>
            <li>Pack-load progression</li>
            <li>Bi-weekly check-ins</li>
            <li>Pre-trip taper &amp; fueling notes</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-ghost">
            Tell me about your trip <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="background: var(--paper-warm);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split">
        <div class="split-text">
          <span class="eyebrow">Who I Work With</span>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 18px;">
            Adults who want to feel like themselves in their bodies for a long
            time.
          </h2>
          <p style="color: var(--granite); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.65; margin-top: 24px;">
            My clients are mostly between thirty and seventy. Some are
            training for a specific peak. Some are training so the next twenty
            winters don't take what the last twenty did. Some are managing a
            chronic condition and want a coach who's been there.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--granite); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.65;">
            If you're looking for shred-and-blast, hype-on-the-floor,
            before-and-after photos — I'm the wrong coach. If you want
            someone who'll show up every week for years and read your body
            the way a good doctor reads a chart, we should talk.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="split-image"
          style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517438476312-10d79c077509?w=1400&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop')"
        >
          <div class="caption">Strength gym · North Shore</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">Logistics</span>
        <h2>The practical part.</h2>
      </div>
      <dl style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr; gap: 28px 48px; max-width: 880px;">
        <dt style="font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; color: var(--granite-soft); font-size: 18px;">Where</dt>
        <dd style="margin: 0; font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink);">
          In person at North Shore Strength &amp; Movement, Beverly, MA. A
          short list of remote-programming clients on a case-by-case basis.
        </dd>
        <dt style="font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; color: var(--granite-soft); font-size: 18px;">When</dt>
        <dd style="margin: 0; font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink);">
          Mornings Tuesday through Saturday. Some evening slots in shoulder
          seasons.
        </dd>
        <dt style="font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; color: var(--granite-soft); font-size: 18px;">First step</dt>
        <dd style="margin: 0; font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink);">
          Always the assessment. Whatever tier you land on, we begin there.
        </dd>
        <dt style="font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; color: var(--granite-soft); font-size: 18px;">Cancellation</dt>
        <dd style="margin: 0; font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink);">
          24-hour notice. Life happens — one make-up per quarter, no questions.
        </dd>
        <dt style="font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; color: var(--granite-soft); font-size: 18px;">Nutrition</dt>
        <dd style="margin: 0; font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink);">
          Out of scope. For medical nutrition therapy I refer out to a
          registered dietitian I trust.
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="background: var(--forest-deep); color: var(--dune-soft); text-align: center;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--dune) 70%, transparent);">
        Start Here
      </span>
      <h2 style="color: var(--paper); margin-top: 16px; max-width: 24ch; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">
        Whichever tier you're considering, the first step is the same.
      </h2>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn" style="background: var(--paper); color: var(--forest-deep); margin-top: 28px;">
        Get in touch <span class="arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
